subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis: 
Yangambia

belongs to the 

Odoniella

- complex (see discussion after tribe) and it can be distinguished from other genera of this group by: scutellum divided into six parts dorsally (
Fig. 11I
), scutellum impunctate (
Fig. 11I
), humeral angles of pronotum distinctly flattened and serrate (
Fig. 10I
); flattened dark setae on hemelytra in parches, and spermathecal gland on DLP placed medially near posterior margin (
Fig. 21C
).
